1. User Profile (GET /api/profile)
   Returns the logged-in user's ID, username, email, role, and join date.
   Protected by JWT. Users only see their own profile. Password/hash never returned.
2. Password Change (PUT /api/change-password)
   Allows logged-in users to change password. Verifies current password,
   ensures new/confirm match, rejects reusing old password, hashes before saving.
3. Admin User Management
   Admin-only endpoints to list all users, update roles, and delete accounts.
   Normal users receive 403 Forbidden. No passwords in responses.
4. Login Attempt Protection
   Tracks failed logins per account. After 5 failures, account is locked for 15 minutes.
   Returns a generic safe message. Resets counter on successful login.
5. Logout (POST /api/logout)
   Revokes the JWT via token blacklisting (stores JTI in database).
   After logout, the token cannot access protected routes.